<br>
I went to EW and tagged two Ulthorks with the TFlux staff.  Things went down hill from there, hehe.  I died, figured out what I did wrong, and tried again.<br>
<br>
Then I went on a quading spree, pulling, pulling pulling.<br>
<br>
God the exp!  6.5 yellow in 2 hours.  Now I am level 38 with less than a yellow to go to level 39.   I keep asking myself why haven't I been doing this since level 34?????<br>
<br>
Most exciting moment was when I got one of those double pop bugs where you have two mobs together that look like one.  Well I pulled what I thought was four Ulthork Warriors and I actually had seven.  I had KEI, but I still had to use harvest and med once to finish them what with the repeated BoF resists and re-snaring.  Thank goodness I had invested in a ten dose SoW potion.  Real lifesaver.<br>
<br>
I am hooked on this for experiencing.  However, I still prefer to group up with friends or guildmates, but this is the way to go to level up for those next spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=szashazwrath7>Szasha Zwrath7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/29/03 3:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=778.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First Quading exp</span><hr size=1> I never even entertained the idea of quading until hitting 40 and going through these forums.  I couldnt manage to kite 1 mob because I was set up all wrong and they would always catch up to me before hotkey spells.  How things are set up makes a big difference between success and failure.<br>
<br>
I got pretty efficient in learning to quad fairly quickly, but find the view thing makes me a bit clutzy.  The best camera view I find to work best is the third person...backing it off a bit so you can see your whole body...this enables you to turn quickly to peek at your aggro without losing too much ground in the process....also I use f9 and toggle to the last view to see an arial view if the mobs are rounded up enough to bond them.  Too bad there is not a way to make a hot key for camera veiws...very annoying indeed.<br>
<br>
The worst thing to happen is 1 or 2 break bonds and then you spend your time scrambling to get them together again...I got sick of doing that, so to play it safe, i recast bonds every third nuke to be sure..and also look at the text to make sure all of them took the snare.  I learned the hard way with that, as I had 4 and 1 would break as soon as I got the other back to the pack.<br>
<br>
If your mobs do separate...a good trick is to get them in a position where you can run right in between two of them without getting hit....then run in a straight line and watch them come together.....  like making them walk a v pattern and meeting in the middle.  I love that one!<br>
<br>
Ew and ulthorks can get pretty crowded, but a fantastic area to learn the art of quading with so much open space and relatively flat open land to manuever in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ygrayne>Ygrayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/2/03 10:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=778.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First Quading exp</span><hr size=1> Bonds is a fixed duration spell.<br>
<br>
Whenever I have a quad where I snare individually or one or more resist, I recast Bonds (or Atol's) on all four so they are all on the same timer, then resnare every 6-8 nukes or so. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=778.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=778.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=778.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.graffe.com/images/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=778.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=778.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=778.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies" align=absmiddle> Click to receive email notification of replies</a><br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=778.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies" align=absmiddle> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a><br> </